All Implemented Interfaces:
Domain, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<Symbol,java.util.HashSet<PointsToRel>>
public class PointsToDomain
extends java.util.LinkedHashMap<Symbol,java.util.HashSet<PointsToRel>>
implements Domain

PointsToDomain represents a set of pointer-relationships at a given program point, and is used by the Points-to Analyzer.

Implements the domain interface used by Cetus analysis passes for easier flexibility and sharing between passes. Specifically implements the merge, union, diff, intersect, kill and clone functionality.

Relationships inside of this domain are represented by PointsToRel.

See Also:
PointsToRel, Domain, Serialized Form

merge

public static Domain merge(Domain s1,
                           Domain s2)
Static method to merge two Points-to domains. Merge must handle types of relationships when combining the two domains, as opposed to a simple union. This functionality is used to combine information coming down different paths, and the new information must reflect the flow from more than one path.

Parameters:
s1 - First domain in the merge
s2 - Second domain in the merge
